{"types":[{"section":"\n{{fr-adj|f=maligne|f2=maline}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|obsolete}} [[nocive]], [[pernicious]]\n# {{lb|fr|medicine}} [[malignant]]\n#: {{ant|fr|bénin}}\n#: {{coi|fr|une tumeur '''maligne'''|a malignant tumor}}\n# {{lb|fr|chiefly|dated|or|biblical}} [[malicious]], [[sadistic]] {{gloss|which likes to do or say hurtful things for fun}}\n#: {{syn|fr|méchant}}\n#: {{coi|fr|prendre un [[malin plaisir|'''malin''' plaisir]] à faire quelque chose|to take perverse pleasure in doing something}}\n# {{lb|fr|informal}} [[smart]] and quick-thinking, and often [[trickster]]ish; [[cunning]], [[crafty]]\n#: {{syn|fr|astucieux|fin|intelligent|rusé}}\n#: {{coi|fr|[[malin comme un singe|'''malin''' comme un singe]]|[[smart as a whip|'''smart''' as a whip]]}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|avoir l'air '''malin'''|to look daft, to look silly|footer=(''ironic'')}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|C'est '''malin''' !|[[well done|Well done]]!}}\n#* {{quote-song|fr|year=1982|title=Un été sans toi|artist=Charles Aznavour|passage=C’est inhumain / De me laisser seul / J’ai l’air '''malin''' / Sous mon parasol|t=It's inhuman / To leave me alone / I '''look silly''' / Under my umbrella}}\n# {{lb|fr|Quebec}} [[aggressive]] {{q|of an animal}}; [[petulant]] {{q|of a person}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* The standard language uses the feminine {{m|fr||maligne}}. The popular byform {{m|fr||maline}} has existed since the 16th century, but is considered incorrect in formal writing. In the vernacular, it is predominant especially for the sense {{m-g|smart, cunning}}.\n* In its meaning of {{m-g|malicious}} the word is mostly restricted to expressions such as {{m|fr||malin plaisir}}; it is a standard attribute of the Devil.\n\n","alt":[],"syn":["méchant","astucieux","fin","intelligent","rusé"],"type":"adj","forms":[{"g":"m","n":"s"}],"html":"<p><span class=\"headword-line\"><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"fr\">malin</strong> (<i>feminine</i> <b class=\"Latn form-of lang-fr f|s-form-of\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/maligne#French\